headline: Flight cuts, consumer sentiment, Miran speech: What to Watch
summary: Market Domination Overtime host Josh Lipton takes a look at the top stories for investors to watch on Friday, Nov. 7. The Federal Aviation Administration (FAA) announced a 10% decrease in air traffic, going into effect on Friday at 40 major airports. More commentary is coming from several Federal Reserve officials, including New York Fed President John Williams and Fed Governor Stephen Miran. Constellation Energy (CEG), Enbridge (ENB), and Duke Energy (DUK) will report quarterly results in the morning. The University of Michigan's preliminary November consumer sentiment reading will be posted in the morning. To watch more expert insights and analysis on the latest market action, check out more Market Domination Overtime.
